metadata.name: MAGNETIK #251
metadata.description:
The output of MAGNETIK reminds me of what tornadoes do to our cities and buildings, yet I imagine the pieces that are about to break off and fly away to be made of metal foil and they do so because of a magnetic force that is pulling them away from where they belong…  This one is also a charity run :  
- 20% of the primary sales will go directly to the Processing Foundation, 

- Remaining 80% will be donated to a group of individuals that raise money to buy computers for less fortunate architecture students in a university in the eastern part of Turkey. Please read the next paragraph for a detailed explanation

- I will decide what to do with the secondary sales later if there will be any.

About the majority (80%) of the donation : I decided that the donations should be done in a double-blind way, the donator does not know who they are donating to, and the receivers of the donation will not know from whom the donation is coming from, hence I will transfer the funds these individuals mentioned to act as a middle-step. I feel like this is a hard thing to provide a solid proof for, so I recommend if you have doubts and/or straight away do not trust me or this process, do not mint. I will only be able to provide proof of transfer of funds to a third-party. I trust the people I am sending the funds to, we have done this before (not to brag or anything) and I know that we are affecting younger people’s life in a good way. Also, I believe that the funds raised from this project alone will not be enough to buy one decent config. computer by itself, if it were so, I would have done it differently.  About MAGNETIK :  
MAGNETIK plays on the idea of distorting and breaking grids by employing an illusion of fake 3D and tries to make the resulting composition look good with rhythm and color harmony.
 
- 21 palettes,
- 2 background modes : lights on / lights off,
- 3 grid types,
- plus some surprise features…

I encourage you to try and see the variations before minting :)  2 of the grid types are based on https://gorillasun.de/blog/an-algorithm-for-irregular-grids by Ahmad Moussa ( https://twitter.com/gorillasu ) and used with his knowledge and kind permission.

gradient formulas are based on https://twitter.com/takawo/status/1505876107492720651?s=20&t=S9aU_oNYyjBieBcEmvUV-g
by Takawo Shunsuke ( https://twitter.com/takawo ) and used with his knowledge and kind permission.

Thank you all in advance and have a good day!

DISCLAIMER : I am not a good coder, I have tried to fix my past mistakes from my earlier projects to make some room for new mistakes :) I am hoping that there isn’t any huge bugs or anything left so you can enjoy your mint! Please hit me up if you have any concerns after minting and we can discuss a solution.

metadata.name: Garden of Imagination #7
metadata.description:
The more a garden can sharpen all senses, the better.

The garden is one of the most artistic expressions where the five human senses are explored (sight, smell, sound, taste and touch).
It's very good to be impressed by many different colors and shapes, feel the perfume of flowers, feel the textures of plants, taste the fruits and hear the noise of leaves and birds. The more a garden manages to sharpen all the senses, the better it fulfills its role.
The challenge of this project is to provide as many sensations as possible, some you will get visually and others you will need imagination. Imagination is an essential part of this project. There are different species from different cultures that, after becoming relatives, start to interact with each other.

The Garden of Imagination is layered artwork generated from a pool of previously rendered digital assets developed for several months.

- Use the "S" key to export an image.

metadata.name: Avoidance #42
metadata.description: Created with Javascript and p5js. Each bar steers clear of the other bars and balls. This is an experiment in which I admittedly invested a little too much time. The numerous variables, factors, and variants ensure that each mint has a distinct outcome.

metadata.name: Ghrian #149
metadata.description:
Dutch auction (13/11/9/6/3), with price decreasing every 10 minutes after the start of the auction until 9 tez. Price will then decrease to 6 tez after 2 hours, then to 3 after 12 hours.

A selection of 33 different palettes.

The brush draw is determined by angles, shapes, randomly chosen overdraws, brush sizes and widths, among other things.

- Left arrow = draw in 2125x1375
- Right arrow = draw in 11x17 landscape mode fit to screen height
- Up arrow = draw in 1375x2125
- Down arrow = draw in 11x17 portrait mode fit to screen width
- Enter = draw in full window
- Tab = draw in 1400x1400
- Shift = draw in 1:1 aspect ratio scaled to window height with 5% border on all sides
- Alt = draw in 1:1 aspect ratio scaled to window height with 5% border on all sides (default pixel density)
- Left mouse click = save as a png

Pixel density is set to 2 for all of the options above unless noted otherwise.

Please note that the drawing can take quite a while to run, especially in the full screen modes.

See thread below for additional details:

https://twitter.com/AndwerEric/status/1492619586931413000?s=20&t=N8joIBuTNzYYjmcBex0QJQ

Sunder: Hills #194
metadata.description:
This is my first experimentation with a new algorithm I call Sunder. The Hill you mint represents you inner-self. It could be colorful, messy, stern, calm, crowded. Reflect on it. I hope you enjoy my work.

Made in p5.js

By twistie

metadata.description:
Bleached dimensions, creamy pixels, colorful apparitions, void zones and uneventful dances. A group of specters (A.K.A. circles that trail) attempt to accompany, comfort, entertain, hypnotize, console and soothe you. 

NOTE: Requires browsers and devices which support Float32 textures. Firefox has been most reliable.

metadata.name: fx_doughs #4552
FairyCells II #281
metadata.description:
FairyCells II is intended as a logical continuation of the first FairyCells series. By dropping the plotter drawing constraint, new perspectives for exploration appeared.
This is how these cells began to intertwine, live together, mutate and change color, like an evolving system.

What surprises me the most in this new series, is the stories appearing behind each new composition. See how these abstracts shapes can come to life and narrate us things through our imagination.

Each color palette takes us into a different world, drawing a very specific atmosphere.

As me, let yourself be carried away by these stories 💫 !

Artwork by Julien_Espagnon, 2022.

Control : Press « S » to save the image as a PNG.

metadata.name: Unicorn #5613
metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. But we're the only ones who can do it. We are those magical unicorns, unique, inimitable, with our own qualities and magical abilities.
These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.
